Description: Repaint only from the change when editing a line
 Every edit brackets its damage to the whole logical line for wrap
 bookkeeping, so each keypress repaints the entire line and typing
 slows as the line grows. Characters before the change never move;
 start the single-row damage at the change position, as the adjacent
 zero-row branch already does, so appending repaints only the tail.
Author: Logan Russell <me@lrussell.net>
--- a/src/FXText.cpp
